parameters: I never would've thought I would
This is the Shrine of Karma.
but maybe my memory's just failing me.
W-wait a moment. The Shrine of Karma?
So you know about it, Tahati.
Where the God of Wind sleeps.
I was one of the spirits who served her.
Ooh, Noizac? That brings back memories.
I wonder if she's doing fine these days.
Miss Tahati, you met a god face-to-face...?
A bit before I created Parlates, yes.
Her disciples were indebted to me.
Actually, how old are you right now?
That's the worst lie I've ever heard.
So Sir Tyvar left her and came here?
Ah, the other spirits who served Her
were so splendid that I had nothing to do
and was basically just wasting my time.
How could you just... leave her?
Of course She approved my leave.
She even bestowed Her power for
If that's so, it'd make sense that...
Noizac was the Sage of Karmic Ode──
And I inherited Her title and powers.
Karmic Ode, the concept of life, death
Sir Tyvar, you repeat the cycle of life over and over,
and can come back to life after dying, yes?
It's normal to come back to life
after death in this world, though.
Karmic Ode and Undeath are different concepts.
I do not "come back to life".
I don't see what's so different.
In a sense, I can understand why you
hated the Reason of Undeath so much.
But── when I think about it more closely,
without the Reason of Undeath, there'd be
nobody else left living but me in the end.
I have to say it was shallow.
I don't like this unnatural process!
I know that the Reason of Undeath is
wholly unnatural. I know full well.
...I don't quite understand the extent of
the Karmic Ode's power, but is it
because of that that Sir Tyvar was able
I don't get it, but good for you.
Okay, that should be enough for
We really just had a quick chat with Tyvar.
That's true, but nothing else is here...
Listening to his stories is quite fun
It's not like I didn't have fun, either...
Well, whatever, let's just go somewhere else.
